title.narrative: IMPROVED CHILD PROTECTION SERVICES (WELFARE - JUSTICE - BR - COMMUNITY)

description.narrative: Child protection service providers and community-based actors are able to prevent, identify, refer and respond to child rights violation, including in humanitarian emergencies, which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children, especially adolescent girls, in vulnerable regions are better protected from violence, abuse, exploitation and harmful practices, including in emergency situations

title.narrative: Child protection service providers and community-based actors are able to prevent, identify, refer and respond to child rightsviolation, including in humanitarian emergencies

description.narrative: By the end of the programme cycle, child protection service providers and community-based actors in the six regions of UNICEF intervention as well as in Yaoundé II were more able to prevent, identify, refer, and respond to child rights violations, including in humanitarian emergencies. Child protection systems as well as birth registration mechanisms in urban and rural areas and at centralized and decentralized levels have been strengthened and assisted more than 404,514 children and caregivers in need of psychosocial support and 116,939 women and children in need of Gender-Based Violence response services. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:02/02/2022
